text:
At least 25 Indian lawmakers tested positive for the coronavirus before the reopening of parliament on Monday — the first time the chambers have been open in nearly 6 months.

name: NPR
text:
Russian President Vladimir Putin announced a $1.5 billion loan for Belarus' struggling economy and reaffirmed existing security guarantees — a limited lifeline for embattled Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko.
https://t.co/1M39ciP6hx

name: NPR
text:
A crowd of more than 100,000 gathered in Minsk on Sunday to demand the resignation of President Alexander Lukashenko over allegations of a rigged election.

Lukashenko's nickname in protest circles is simply "the rat."

A standard chant: "leave."
https://t.co/PdyokcpQbq
